<subSubSection id="C33CA9C7FFA1FFD6A88EFEFDB872C3DD" pageId="5" pageNumber="370" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="8B99FA4CFFA1FFD6A88EFEFDB872C3DD" blockId="5.[1482,2689,289,476]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis id="B952265EFFA1FFD6A88EFEFDB83AC368" bold="true" box="[1484,1842,289,318]" pageId="5" pageNumber="370">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List (under 
<taxonomicName id="4C2681CFFFA1FFD6A88DFE94B9EEC333" baseAuthorityName="Lesson" baseAuthorityYear="1826" box="[1487,1766,328,357]" class="Mammalia" family="Bathyergidae" genus="Cryptomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="370" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hottentotus">Cryptomys hottentotus</taxonomicName>
). Data are deficient for an accurate determination of the conservation status of Whyte’s Mole-rat.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
